Wootton Bassett, who defied his minnow start at stud in France to become one of Europe&rsquo;s most sought after proven stallions, will shuttle to Australia later this year, less than 12 months after coming under the ownership of the powerful Coolmore empire.&nbsp;<br />
<br />
After running a teaser campaign at the weekend, Coolmore principal Tom Magnier confirmed Wootton Bassett would join the stud&rsquo;s Australian roster at Jerrys Plains later this year, standing alongside the likes of fellow shuttlers Justify and American Pharoah.&nbsp;

